    "problemStatement": "You are given the heights of the students of a class consisting of nnn students. Your task is to find the maximum length of an increasing subarray of the given array.\n\nA subarray is the sequence of consecutive elements of the array. Subarray is called increasing if each element of this subarray is strictly greater than the previous.\n\n\nInput Format\nThe first line contains a single positive integer nnn — the number of students.\n\n\nThe second line contains nnn positive integers a1,a2,...,ana1,a2,...,ana1,a2,...,an - the heights of students.\n\n\n\nOutput Format\nPrint the maximum length of an increasing subarray of the given array.",
    "constraints": [
      "1≤n≤1051 \\leq n \\leq 10^51≤n≤105",
      "2≤ai≤1092 \\leq ai \\leq 10^92≤ai≤109"
    ],
